y in mountain view calif their employer william shockley had decided not to continue research into siliconbased semiconductors frustrated they decided to undertake the work on their own the researchers — who would become known as the traitorous eight — went on to invent the microprocessor and to found intel among other companies  a legal bridge spanning  years from the gold mines of el dorado to the golden startups of silicon valley by gregory gromov  crystal fire p   boyer edward j  august  controversial nobel laureate shockley dies los angeles times retrieved  may    evolution cannot occur unless favorable genes are segregated out from amongst unfavorable genetic formulae  any population that adopts a perverted or dysgenic form of altruism – one which encourages a breeding community to breed disproportionately those of its members who are genetically handicapped rather than from those who are genetically favored or which aids rival breeding populations to expand while restricting its own birthrate – is unlikely to survive into the definite future – pearson roger b the concept of heredity in western thought part three the revival of interest in genetics the mankind quarterly  pp    pearson roger  shockley on eugenics and race pg – scotttownsend publishers isbn   bio of edgar epps httpeducationillinoisedu university of illinois retrieved  january   external link in website help  epps edgar g jan–february  racism science and the iq integrated education   – doi  check date values in date help  polly morrice  the genius factory testtube superbabies the new york times retrieved    kessler ronald absent at the creation how one scientist made off with the biggest invention since the light bulb   shurkin  pp – essentially the jury agreed that witherspoons column met the standards of defamation but that by then shockleys reputation wasnt worth very much  shurkin  p   william shockley still controversial after all these years   crystal fire p  william b shockley  creator of 