 let alone that of genius  it seems clear that these data powerfully confirm the suspicion that intelligence is not a sufficient trait for truly creative achievement of the highest grade referencesedit brittain je  becker and shive on the transistor proceedings of the ieee    issn  doiproc retrieved  january  an observation that william shockley interpreted as confirmation of his concept of that junction transistor  eysenck hans  intelligence a new look new brunswick nj transaction publishers isbn   giangreco d m  casualty projections for the us invasions of japan  planning and policy implications journal of military history    issn  doi  goodheart adam  july   days that changed history new york times retrieved  january   leslie mitchell july–august  the vexing legacy of lewis terman stanford magazine retrieved  june   park gregory lubinski david benbow camilla p  november  recognizing spatial intelligence scientific american retrieved  june   shurkin joel  broken genius the rise and fall of william shockley creator of the electronic age london macmillan isbn  lay summary  june   simonton dean keith  origins of genius darwinian perspectives on creativity oxford oxford university press isbn  lay summary  august   riordan michael hoddeson lillian  crystal fire the invention of the transistor and the birth of the information age sloan technology series new york norton isbn  lay summary – technology and culture review by arthur p molella  december   saxon wolfgang  august  william b shockley  creator of transistor and theory on race new york times retrieved  january  he drew further scorn when he proposed financial rewards for the genetically disadvantaged if they volunteered for sterilization  shockley william  contributors to proceedings of the ire proceedings of the ire   httpieeexploreieeeorgstampstampjsparnumber sparks morgan hogan lester linville john  obituary william shockley physics today   – bibcodephtfs issn  doi  tucker william h  first published  the fundin